        "summaryHtml": "<p><strong>The Millionaire Fastlane </strong></p><p><strong>MJ DeMarco</strong></p><p>Year: 2011<br />Publisher: </p><p>Pages: 334</p><p><strong><br />About </strong></p><p>This book is a contrarian approach to wealth, encouraging entrepreneurship, smart risk-taking, and financial leverage to achieve rapid income growth and escape traditional slow-lane paths to riches.</p><p><strong>Product Description</strong></p><p>Since you were old enough to hold a job, you've been hoodwinked into believing that wealth can be created by blindly trusting in the uncontrollable and unpredictable markets: the housing market, the stock market, and the job market. This soul-sucking, dream-stealing dogma is known as the \"The Slowlane\" - a risky financial gamble that dubiously promises wealth in a wheelchair.</p><p>Accept the Slowlane as your financial roadmap and your financial future will blow carelessly asunder on a sailboat of HOPE: HOPE you can get a job and keep it, HOPE the stock market doesn't tank, HOPE for a robust economy, HOPE, HOPE, and HOPE. Do you really want HOPE as the centerpiece for your family's financial plan?</p><p>Drive the Slowlane and you will discover your life deteriorate into a miserable exhibition about what you cannot do versus what you can. For those who refuse the lifetime subscription to mediocrity, there's an expressway to extraordinary wealth capable of burning a trail to financial freedom faster than any road out there. </p><p>And shockingly, this road has nothing to do with jobs, 401(k)s, indexed-funds, or a lifestyle of miserly living in a tiny house. Just some of what you will learn: NEWSFLASH! Your mainstream financial guru who's on 500 radio stations and lives in a $10,000,000 mansion isn't rich because he religiously follows his own advice-- he's rich because he's sold it to enough fools who believe it... in other words, he's driving The Millionaire Fastlane.</p><p>Demand more. Demand the truth.</p><p>Change lanes and find your explosive wealth accelerator. Hit the Fastlane, crack the code to wealth, and educate yourself on living rich for a lifetime.</p><ul><li>Why jobs, 401(k)s, indexed-funds, and 40-years of mindless frugality will never make you rich young.</li><li>Why most entrepreneurs fail and how to immediately put the odds in your favor.</li><li>The real law of wealth: Leverage this, and wealth has no choice but to be magnetized to you.</li><li>The leading cause of poorness: Change this, and you change everything.</li><li>How the rich really get rich - and no, it has nothing to do with a paycheck or a 401K match.</li><li>The indisputable mathematics of wealth: how you and any \"Joe Schmo\" can tap into real wealth real fast.</li><li>Why the guru's sacred deities - compound interest and indexed fund investing - are impotent wealth accelerators.</li><li>Why popular guru platitudes like \"do what you love\" and \"follow your passion\" will most likely keep you poor, not rich.</li><li>And 250+ more poverty-busting distinctions...</li><li>10TH ANNIVERSARY EDITION</li></ul><p><strong>Selective Summary</strong></p><p>This book is a guide to accelerating wealth creation by adopting unconventional strategies. DeMarco explains that relying solely on traditional paths like employment and slow saving often delays financial independence.</p><p>Readers learn to identify opportunities with high growth potential, leverage systems, and create scalable income sources. The book emphasizes mindset, entrepreneurship, and disciplined action. DeMarco stresses the importance of avoiding consumer debt, managing risks, and making deliberate investment choices.</p><p>Practical guidance includes financial planning, investing strategies, and building assets that generate passive income. Readers are encouraged to focus on long-term results, think creatively, and pursue multiple income streams.</p><p>By the end, readers gain a roadmap for achieving wealth faster than conventional approaches allow. DeMarco demonstrates that with strategy, focus, and calculated risk-taking, financial freedom is attainable sooner than most people believe.</p><p><strong>Book Reviews</strong></p><p>Rating: 4.7 | (14,258)<br /></p><p>Top comments: </p><p>1. “This is by far the best book ever written on the subject, better than Rich Dad Poor Dad, better than Think and Grow Rich, better than any book by Donald Trump...” – Amazon reader review</p><p>2. “You'll learn more in 2 days from this book than you will in 2 years of business college courses...” – Amazon reader review</p><p>3. “There are moments in your life where a light bulb just seems to turn on, a switch just seems to flip. If you're looking to induce one of these, look no further than this book.” – Amazon reader review</p><p>4. “I can promise you that there is a clarity that comes with reading this book that no other book on the market will ever give you.” –  Amazon reader review</p><p>5. “The best book on acquiring wealth ever written...” – Amazon reader review</p><p><strong>Indicative Price: $24.52</strong></p><p><strong>BUY NOW</strong></p>"
