        "summaryHtml": "<p><strong>The 7 Habits of Highly Effective People </strong></p><p><strong>Stephen R. Covey</strong></p><p>Year: 2020<br />Publisher: Simon & Schuster</p><p>Pages: 496</p><p><strong><br />About </strong></p><p>This book by Stephen R. Covey introduces timeless habits that transform effectiveness, teaching principles of responsibility, vision, prioritization, communication, and renewal for personal and professional success.</p><p><strong>Product Description</strong></p><p>None Found.</p><p><strong>Selective Summary</strong></p><p>This book outlines a framework for personal and professional effectiveness through seven habits that transform character and behavior. Covey emphasizes that true success stems from aligning one’s life with timeless principles such as integrity, responsibility, and mutual respect.</p><p>The first three habits focus on personal mastery: being proactive, beginning with the end in mind, and putting first things first. These habits encourage individuals to take control of their choices, clarify their vision, and prioritize actions that align with long-term goals rather than immediate distractions.</p><p>The next three habits emphasize relationships and collaboration: thinking win-win, seeking first to understand then to be understood, and synergizing. These habits build trust, empathy, and cooperation, fostering effective teamwork and problem-solving.</p><p>The seventh habit, “sharpen the saw,” stresses the importance of continuous renewal through physical, mental, emotional, and spiritual growth. Covey argues that effectiveness is not a one-time achievement but an ongoing process of self-improvement and balance.</p><p>Covey also highlights the shift from dependence to independence, and ultimately to interdependence, as the foundation of maturity. By mastering personal responsibilities and then collaborating effectively with others, individuals can achieve lasting success.</p><p>The book provides practical tools, reflections, and principles that help readers build discipline, strengthen relationships, and lead with purpose. It remains a timeless guide for aligning daily actions with core values, showing that effectiveness is about character-driven living rather than quick fixes.</p><p><strong>Book Reviews</strong></p><p>Rating: 4.7 (15,100)\t<br /></p><p>Top comments: </p><p>1. “Must-Have for your Book Collection!” – SherwinE</p><p>2. “Second time reading this book. It's amazing.” – Joan</p><p>3. “I first encountered that book, thanks to some very dear friends of mine, when I was going through some personal turmoil. That book truly saved my life. Since then, I have read it a lot of times, and purchased it for special people who have entered my life throughout the years. Its simplicity, and common sense. will stun you, in a positive way. 10/10” – AlexF</p><p>4. “Great book founded on timeless principles” – noah mhlanga</p><p>5. “Timeless book for the ages. One of the key 'habits', doing the important not urgent things first, is practically what the '5am club' rip-off book takes a whole tedious book to espouse..RIP Steven Covey...” – Musicislife</p><p><strong>Indicative Price: $</strong> <strong>26.95</strong></p><p><strong>BUY NOW</strong></p>"
