        "amazonUrl": "https://www.amazon.com.au/s?k=The%20Making%20of%20a%20Manager&tag=carl0c72-20",
        "summaryHtml": "<p><strong>The Making of a Value Investor: What a bear market taught me about investing </strong></p><p><strong>Gautam Baid</strong></p><p>Year: 2023<br />Publisher: HarperCollins</p><p>Pages: 288</p><p><strong><br />About </strong></p><p>This book shows how the lessons of a bear market shape disciplined investing, stressing patience, rational decision-making, resilience, and the importance of focusing on long-term business fundamentals over short-term market swings.</p><p><strong>Product Description</strong></p><p><em>The Making of a Value Investor </em>follows Gautam Baid's development as an investor during a brutal bear market, when he recorded his reflections, observations and learnings in his investment journal in the face of an increasingly uncertain future. This book charts the mistakes and successes in the battle for investment survival during one of the most tumultuous market phases in history.</p><p>Through time travel-like storytelling, Baid skilfully captures his collective experiences of that period, allowing readers to truly connect with his evolving worldview. The entries from his journal presented in a chronological manner, with added retrospective commentary, are a treasure trove of everlasting investment principles. The result is a book that provides you invaluable lessons on navigating financial markets and building resilience.</p><p><strong>Selective Summary</strong></p><p><strong>Book Reviews</strong></p><p>Rating: 4.2 | (205)<br /></p><p>Top comments: </p><p>1. “The journal unfolds his personal learning, highlighting his own victories and failures and making his way through the bear market and rising above all. Baid's storytelling, akin to a journey through time, skillfully immerses readers in his evolving worldview. The chronological presentation of journal entries, accompanied by insightful retrospective commentary, opens up a treasure trove of timeless investment principles.” – Arun Verma</p><p>2. “Full of insights and observations about the equity markets in India. If information is X, then knowledge is X raised to the power of 2, and experience is X raised to the power of 3, and insights is X raised to the power of 4. Information is a commodity and freely available and hence has no value in today’s world. On the other end of the scale is insight that only comes with experience and is of infinite value. This is what this worthy book is all about. I am looking forward to more learning from this esteemed author in the coming years as he is quite young and has a long runway in front of him.” – VIVEK SHIVDASANI</p><p>3. “It has taken me through the bear market in India from 2018 till 2020 and into the mind of an investor who has travelled through this bear market; emotional swings, course corrections undertaken, and learnings of the Author was vividly explained in this book day wise and those were really useful for a new investor like me;” – Amazon Customer</p><p>4. “It's good to relive the past ...the data is awesome and the emotions involved are great ..While many things the author thinks are not top drawer ...like diversification...If you know what you are doing you do not diversify...from time to time your portfolio will go down by 50 percent ...It is in the nature of the game.....Very good book” – anonymous</p><p>5. “Insightful Content. Great book to read. I highly recommend this book.” – Arghya Mukherjee</p><p><strong>Indicative Price: $24.60</strong></p><p><strong>BUY NOW</strong></p>"
