        "amazonUrl": "https://www.amazon.com.au/s?k=Business%20Made%20Simple&tag=carl0c72-20",
        "summaryHtml": "<p><strong>Business Made Simple: 60 Days to Master Leadership, Sales, Marketing, Execution, Management, Personal Productivity and More </strong></p><p><strong>Donald Miller</strong></p><p>Year: 2021<br />Publisher: HarperCollins Leadership US</p><p>Pages: 240</p><p><strong><br />About </strong></p><p>This book is a structured program delivers actionable lessons and practical frameworks to quickly improve business skills, decision-making, and productivity across multiple domains.</p><p><strong>Product Description</strong></p><p>New York Times and Wall Street Journal bestselling author, Donald Miller knows that business is more than just a good idea made profitable – it’s a system of unspoken rules, rarely taught by MBA schools. If you are attempting to profitably grow your business or career, you need elite business knowledge—knowledge that creates tangible value.</p><p>Even if you had the time, access, or money to attend a Top 20 business school, you would still be missing the practical knowledge that propels the best and brightest forward. However, there is another way to achieve this insider skill development, which can both drastically improve your career earnings and the satisfaction of achieving your goals.</p><p>Donald Miller learned how to rise to the top using the principles he shares in this book. He wrote Business Made Simple to teach others what it takes to grow your career and create a company that is healthy and profitable.</p><p>These short, daily entries and accompanying videos will add enormous value to your business and the organization you work for. In this sixty-day guide, readers will be introduced to the nine areas where truly successful leaders and their businesses excel:</p><ul><li>Character: What kind of person succeeds in business</li><li>Leadership: How do you unite a team around a mission</li><li>Personal Productivity: How can you get more done in less time</li><li>Messaging: Why aren’t customers paying more attention</li><li>Marketing: How do I build a sales funnel</li><li>Business Strategy: How does a business really work</li><li>Execution: How can we get things done</li><li>Sales: How do I close more sales</li><li>Management: What does a good manager do</li></ul><p>Business Made Simple is the must-have guide for anyone who feels lost or overwhelmed by the modern business climate, even if they attended business school. Learn what the most successful business leaders have known for years through the simple but effective secrets shared in these pages.</p><p><strong>Selective Summary</strong></p><p>Miller explains that business success requires mastering fundamental skills in leadership, sales, marketing, execution, and personal productivity. He emphasizes practical frameworks and step-by-step guidance to quickly develop competence in essential business areas.</p><p>The book highlights clarity and structure. Miller shows that creating clear goals, organized processes, and consistent messaging improves performance, team alignment, and customer engagement.</p><p>A central theme is actionable learning. Miller demonstrates that theory alone is insufficient; implementing strategies, measuring results, and adjusting actions are crucial for business growth. He emphasizes habits, accountability, and focusing on high-leverage activities.</p><p>Practical guidance includes templates, exercises, and techniques for marketing, sales funnels, project management, and personal productivity. Miller stresses prioritization, execution, and disciplined follow-through to achieve measurable outcomes.</p><p>The central idea is that mastering key business skills systematically enables individuals and organizations to increase revenue, efficiency, and impact. By applying clear methods consistently, anyone can accelerate business growth and personal effectiveness.</p><p><strong>Book Reviews</strong></p><p>Rating: 4.7 | (2,065)<br /></p><p>Top comments: </p><p>1. “Donald Miller writes clear, actionable books full of real yet simple and straightforward steps you can take to make your life and business better. This is no exception. I will be perpetually reading this book to continually make the incremental improvements it is jam packed with.” – Clint</p><p>2. “Great to have the book with matching videos including tips. It show how to become a value driven professional which also helps the business.” – Matthew Bulat</p><p>3. “It is very doable and clear. Highly recommend. The videos that go along with the book support and are welcomed added value.” – John A. Crawford</p><p>4. “This business book delivers the equivalent of a 4-year business degree without the college expense. The tips are well explained and come with actionable plans. Definitely worth reading for anyone looking to gain in-depth business insights and practical strategies at minimal cost.” – RobyntheSpeaker</p><p>5. “Get this and ALL his other books. Simply brilliant!” – Mr Peter A</p><p><strong>Indicative Price: $41.90</strong></p><p><strong>BUY NOW</strong></p>"
